ZCZC GE91
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 132300 UTC
ON TUESDAY EVENING A FRONTAL WAVE LIES CLOSE TO NW SCOTLAND WITH LOW 990
NEAR CAPE WRATH. AT THE SAME TIME RIDGE CONDITIONS ARE ACROSS MUCH OF IBERIA
AND FRANCE.
THROUGH WEDNESDAY THE FRONTAL WAVE AND ASSOCIATED LOW MOV E INTO SCANDINAVIA
DPN WITH A STRG NW AIRFLOW DEVELOPING ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES AND SURROUNDING
SEA AREAS. THROUGH THURSDAY AND INTO FRIDAY A WEAK RIDGE BUILDS ACROSS THE
BRITISH ISLES AS A NEW ATLANTIC LOW MOVS E THEN SE APPROACHING WERN IRELAND
LATER FRIDAY.
THE ASSOCIATED FRONTAL TROUGH MOV ERRATICALLY E INTO SW PORTPATRICK AND
W NITON. STRG TO GALE FORCE WINDS FOR MUCH OF CULLERCOATS WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY
WITH SEV GALES LIKELY FOR A TIME IN THE N AND E FM LATE WEDNESDAY.
WINDS EASE LATER THURSDAY IN WERNMOST SEA AREAS WITH THESE LIGHTER WINDS
THEN EXTENDING E ACROSS REMAINING SEA AREAS THROUGH FRIDAY. HOWEVER FURTHER
STRG WINDS MAY EXTEND TO THE EERN ENGLISH CHANNEL LATER FRIDAY
